Title: WINDOW / GLASS: BACK DOOR GLASS: INSTALLATION; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

INSTALLATION

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL NO. 3 BACK WINDOW GLASS SPACER

(a) Using a brush or sponge, coat the installation area of a new No. 3 back window glass spacer with glass primer.

NOTICE:

  • Do not apply too much glass primer.
  • Allow the glass primer to dry for 3 minutes or more.
  • Throw away any leftover glass primer.

HINT:

If an area other than specified is coated by accident, wipe off the glass primer with a clean piece of cloth before it dries.

(b) Install the new No. 3 back window glass spacer to the back window fix glass as shown in the illustration.

*A

Back Side

*a

Ceramic Notch

HINT:

7. INSTALL BACK WINDOW FIX GLASS SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Position the back window fix glass sub-assembly.

(1) Using suction cups, place the back window fix glass sub-assembly in the correct position.

(2) Check that the whole contact surface of the back window fix glass sub-assembly rim is perfectly even.

(3) Align the matchmarks on the back window fix glass sub-assembly and back door panel.

NOTICE:

Check that the No. 3 and No. 4 back window glass spacers are engaged to the back door panel correctly.

(4) Remove the back window fix glass sub-assembly.

*a

Matchmark

(b) Using a brush, coat the installation surfaces on the back door panel with body primer.

NOTICE:

  • Do not coat the adhesive with body primer.
  • Do not apply too much body primer.
  • Allow the body primer to dry for 3 minutes or more.
  • Throw away any leftover body primer.

HINT:

If an area other than specified is coated by accident, wipe off the body primer with a clean piece of cloth before it dries.

(c) Using a brush or sponge, coat the adhesive application area with glass primer.

*A

  • Apply glass primer to the ceramic notches.
  • If an area other than specified is coated by accident, wipe off the glass primer with a clean piece of cloth before it dries.

(d) Apply adhesive to the back window fix glass sub-assembly.

Adhesive:

Toyota Genuine Windshield Glass Adhesive or equivalent

(1) Cut off the tip of the cartridge nozzle as shown in the illustration.

Standard Dimension:

Area

Dimension

12.0 to 15.0 mm (0.472 to 0.591 in.)

(3) Apply adhesive to the back window fix glass sub-assembly as shown in the illustration.

Dimension

HINT:

Apply adhesive to the ceramic notches.

(e) Install the back window fix glass sub-assembly.

(1) Using suction cups, position the back window fix glass sub-assembly so that the matchmarks are aligned, and press it in gently along the rim.

NOTICE:

  • Check that the No. 3 and No. 4 back window glass spacers are engaged to the back door panel correctly.
  • Check the clearance between the back door panel and back window fix glass sub-assembly.

*a

Matchmark

(2) Lightly press the outer surface of the back window fix glass sub-assembly to ensure a close fit.

HINT:

Press the glass with force of 98 N (10 kgf, 22.0 lbf) or more.

(3) Using a scraper, remove any excess or protruding adhesive.

(4) Hold the back window fix glass sub-assembly using protective tape until the applied adhesive becomes hard.

HINT:

Follow the instructions supplied by the adhesive manufacturer or in the corresponding instruction manual for the minimum amount of time necessary to wait before driving the vehicle.

(f) Connect each connector.

14. INSTALL BACK DOOR GLASS SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Position the back door glass sub-assembly.

(1) Using suction cups, place the back door glass sub-assembly in the correct position.

(2) Check that the whole contact surface of the back door glass sub-assembly rim is perfectly even.

(3) Align the matchmarks on the back door glass sub-assembly and back door panel.

NOTICE:

Check that the No. 1 and No. 2 back window glass spacers are engaged to the back door panel correctly.

(4) Remove the back door glass sub-assembly.

*a

Matchmark

(b) Using a brush, coat the installation surfaces on the back door panel with body primer.

NOTICE:

  • Do not coat the adhesive with body primer.
  • Do not apply too much body primer.
  • Allow the body primer to dry for 3 minutes or more.
  • Throw away any leftover body primer.

HINT:

If an area other than specified is coated by accident, wipe off the body primer with a clean piece of cloth before it dries.

(c) Using a brush or sponge, coat the adhesive application area with glass primer.

17. INSPECT FOR LEAK

(a) After the adhesive has hardened, apply water from the outside of the vehicle. Check that no water leaks into the cabin.

(b) If water leaks into the cabin, allow the water to dry and add adhesive.

(c) Remove the protective tape.
